summary:
Kotlin is a new statically typed programming language developed by JetBrains, targeting JVM and JavaScript. Kotlin on the JVM is designed to be fully Java compatible, and at the same time safer, more concise than Java and not requiring a PhD to fully understand. Kotlin is developed with IDE support from the very beginning.

Kotlin is currently available as a preview release at http://www.jetbrains.com/kotlin/

During the presentation, we will give an overview of the language and demonstrate the IDE support capabilities. The features we’re planning to cover include:
first-class functions (closures);
extension functions;
operator overloading;
pattern matching;
null safety and automatic casts.
